(3822, 1, '2018-04-04 12:17:42', '2018-04-04 12:17:42', '[vc_row el_id="course4id" el_class="corse4cls"][vc_column css_animation="fadeInLeft" css=".vc_custom_1522312920777{background-image: url(http://localhost/kayaka/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/hdNt-2.jpg?id=3677) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}" el_id="c1id" el_class="c1cls"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1522312948172{background-color: #f4f4f4 !important;}" el_id="hdid" el_class="hdcls"][vc_column][vc_tta_tabs active_section="1" css_animation="fadeIn" el_id="contid" el_class="contclass"][vc_tta_section i_position="right" i_icon_fontawesome="fa fa-desktop" add_icon="true" title="Course Info" tab_id="1522240189758-b560af7d-ab63"][vc_column_text css_animation="none"]\r\n<h3 style="text-align: center;"><strong>HARDWARE &amp; NETWORKING\r\n</strong></h3>\r\nHardware &amp; Networking course are for under graduates and Graduates to build a solid Foundation in computer field. Hardware and Networking is a vast field in India. It is refers to the process of supplying data and information by linking the group of networks using hardware’s devices. To be more specific, hardware networking includes all peripherals, computers, interface cards and other tools required for communications and data processing in the network. [/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section i_position="right" i_icon_fontawesome="fa fa-info-circle" add_icon="true" title="Course Details" tab_id="1522240189931-9ce6ea30-27dc"][vc_column_text css_animation="none"]\r\n<h3 style="text-align: center;"><strong>COURSE DETAILS</strong></h3>\r\nBeginning with Contents like\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Basic Electronics</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Analog &amp; Digital Electronics</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Micro Processor</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Chipsets</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Special Peripherals &amp; I/O Devices</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><